New Idea: ```json{
  "Idea": "We propose RefineManifold: a model-agnostic post-processing framework that reframes summary refinement as a continuous geometric transformation in a learned correction space, rather than discrete module invocation. Unlike prior approaches that rely on fixed corrective subnetworks activated by a router, RefineManifold maps diagnostic signals extracted from a Structured Intermediate Representation (SIR) directly into directional vectors within a unified refinement manifold—a low-dimensional latent space where each axis corresponds to interpretable editing tendencies such as 'increase factual grounding,' 'improve discourse flow,' or 'reduce redundancy.' The SIR, constructed as a belief graph using off-the-shelf NLI models, coreference resolvers, and entity linkers, encodes semantic propositions and their relationships across the source document and generated summary. From this graph, we extract a rich feature vector capturing contradiction density, attribution gaps, repetition patterns, and coherence deficits. A lightweight diagnosis encoder then projects these features into the refinement manifold, producing a correction vector that specifies both the magnitude and combination of desired edits. A generative corrector—implemented as a small, frozen language model with input-adaptive instance normalization—is conditioned on this vector to apply smooth, gradient-based transformations to the original summary tokens. Crucially, the entire system is trained end-to-end on a multi-source dataset annotated with human corrections and corresponding error profiles, learning to map diagnostic states to optimal correction directions without requiring per-module supervision. Because the refinement occurs in a continuous space, interventions are inherently composable and scalable: for example, a summary with moderate hallucination and low coherence receives a blended correction signal, avoiding abrupt transitions between discrete modes. This design eliminates the brittleness of hard routing decisions and allows zero-shot generalization to unseen error combinations. Furthermore, the refinement manifold itself serves as an interpretable audit trail: users can visualize the correction trajectory and even manually adjust the intensity of specific editing dimensions. RefineManifold integrates seamlessly with any black-box summarizer—including commercial APIs—and operates entirely post-hoc, making it ideal for deployment in regulated environments like healthcare or legal tech where traceability and consistency are paramount. By unifying diagnosis and correction in a geometric framework, our method achieves higher precision in targeted editing, reduces side effects, and enables adaptive refinement tuned to domain-specific priorities through simple reweighting of manifold dimensions.",
  "Title": "RefineManifold: Continuous Geometric Refinement of Abstractive Summaries via Diagnosis-Driven Latent Transformations",
